### Describe the bug

Calling `ElementReference.FocusAsync()` does not focus a div element that has a tab index. This is verified by using the CSS selector `:focus` to visually show if the div is focused or not, by changing the background colour. 

If you manually click on the div element, the CSS selector is applied.

This has also been confirmed when using the event `@onfocus` (it's never called until manually focused).

### Expected Behavior

The referenced div is focused.

### Steps To Reproduce

```cs
<button @onclick="Focus">Focus</button>

<div @ref="_reference" tabindex="0" @onblur="Hide" @onfocus="Focused">Hello World</div>

@code {
    private ElementReference _reference;

    private async Task Focus()
    {
        await _reference.FocusAsync();
    }

    private void Focused()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Focused");
    }
}
```

### Exceptions (if any)

_No response_

### .NET Version

.NET 6

